result.execSummary:
The defendant Jack G Trebtoske was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Called at 1:55 PM. Jack Trebtoske appears in person and in custody with attorney Thomas Roley. State appears by Charles Simono. State - matter is resolved - have complied with victim notification requirements- amend count #1  misd theft contrary to 943.20(1)(a) - reads new penalties - joint recommendation of a withheld sentence and place on probation for 12 months, not have talked about conditions except for: restitution of $1376.00 plus $137.60 in VW surcharge totalling $1513.60 - joint and several with co-defendant Ryan Sheldon, DRI counts #2 and #3. Trebtoske and Roley agree. Court dismisses and reads in counts #2 and #3. Court amends count #1 to misd theft contrary to 943.20(1)(a) - reads new penalties. Trebtoske pleads NC to amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation - ask court to consider a condition that the defendant attend school every day that it is in session and no contact with Ryan Sheldon or victim (V.L.) Roley - follow joint recommendation. Trebtoske withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 1 year with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars, costs - paid thru probation, DNA costs - paid thru probation, restitution total of $1513.60 - joint and several with 14CF102 - paid thru probation, participate and successfully complete an anger managment session, obtain HS diploma and attend school every day school is in session and do all work assigned and not to skip school, no contact with Ryan Sheldon or victim (V.L.), right to appeal, adjourned. State - 14TR470 - moves to dismiss for stated reasons. Court dismisses 14TR470.

Called at 3:29 PM. Also called 14CF85. Jack Trebtoske appears in person and in custody with counsel Thomas Roley. State appears by Charles Simono.  State - believe the PH will be waived to due a potential plea/offer and no jail in this case. Trebtoske and Roley agree that the offer weighed into the decision to waive the PH today. Court goes thru waiver of PH collaquey, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. Roley has Information that mirrors complaint, waives reading, enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, set for FPT on 10/15/14 at 1:30 PM. Roley makes argument for bond reduction - asks for signature bond for stated reasons. State - no objections. Court - bond - modifies to $2500.00 signature bond with no consumption of alcohol and no contact with victim.

Called at 2:14 PM. Also called 14CF101. Jack Trebtoske appears in person and in custody and with counsel Thomas Roley. State appears by Charles Simono. Roley would like time to talk to the defendant regarding the plea offer. Recess to do so. Recalled at 2:29 PM with same appearances. Roley would like to address both cases together, has received the new complaint and has gone over it with the defendant, waives formal reading, requests PH within time limits. Court sets for PH on 9/3/14 at 3:00 PM. Roley asks that this matter be set over to 9/3/14 at same time for a possible global resolution. State asks about 14CM97. Court keeps that matter on the 9/12/14 JT date that it is currently set for. Court sets 14CF85 for another FPT on 9/3/14 at 3:00 PM and continues bond on that matter. Roley asks for bond reduction on new case for stated reasons. State - bond - objects to bond modification for stated reasons - if resides at home. Roley responds - asks that the court allow the mother to make a statement. Mom makes statement. Discussion on how school will be accomplished for the defendant has he is currently a senior at Laona High School. Roley makes another argument for signature bond. Court - bond - continues bond at this point on 14CF101.
Preliminary hearing on September 3, 2014 at 03:00 pm.
Adjourned initial appearance on August 27, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Called at 10:21 AM. Jack Trebtoske appears via video from FOSO and without counsel. State appears by Jodie Bednar-Clemens. Trebtoske does not have the complaint. Court reads charges and penalties and right to attorney and court appointed attorney. Trebtoske understands charges, has Tom Roley on his other matters. Court instructs the defendant to re-contact SPD regarding representation on this matter. Court continues bond, set for AIA on 8/27/14 at 1:30 PM, informs defendant to let SPD know of this date.
